         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Sunday 24/4/70. ¶  ¶ Your most kind letter, good and dear Dr Story, has given me great consolation. You speak with as much piety as philosophy, in both of which I can learn much from you. ¶  ¶ Let me ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">70.04.24</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Story</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">DX19 Cotton/Story Papers, University of Tasmania Archives, Hobart.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">Check bot. names.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Sunday 24/4/70.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your most kind letter, good and dear Dr Story, has given me great consolation. You speak with as much piety as philosophy, in both of which I can learn much from you.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me hope, you are well, and that you do not incur unnecessarily the inclemencies of this wet autumn.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have not yet over come my departmental difficulties, but my prospect seems to be brighter again.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Potamogeton<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">1664 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">above </seg>Potamogeton<seg style="font-style: italic; "> in Story's hand.</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">Or: 1664 </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; font-weight: bold; ">interlined by Story</seg>
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> sent by you without flowers &amp; fruits belongs to the series of P. nataces L., common in Britain. But the Australian species has never yet been carefully compared &amp; studied in all its stages.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Myriophyllum<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">6135 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">above </seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Myriophyllum<seg style="font-style: italic; "> in Story's hand.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> cannot be determined without flowers and fruits. It seems however M. variifolium. The Myriophyllum,<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">6135 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">above</seg> Myriophyllum <seg style="font-style: italic; ">in Story's hand.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> named after me is generally a much smaller plant and grows in brackish flats.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The 2 other plants are Utricularia<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">4193 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">above </seg>Utricularia<seg style="font-style: italic; "> in Story's hand.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> dichotoma Labill. and Spiranthes<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">1559 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">above</seg> Spiranthes<seg style="font-style: italic; "> in Story's hand.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> Australis Lindley.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will be happy to give Mr Abbott, when he comes here, also the plants for you.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With best regards</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your attached</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by Story: 'Memo 24/4/70 Potamogeton reqd in flr &amp; fruit'.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
